-- Canadian fund manager AGF plans 70 pct cut in quarterly dividend
-- By Ashutosh Pandey in Bengaluru
-- Tue Dec 09, 2014 09:05AM EST
-- None



Dec 9 (Reuters) - Canadian fund manager AGF Management Ltd <AGFb.TO> said it planned to slash its quarterly dividend by 70 percent to 8 Canadian cents per share, the first cut since 1989.

The company said the planned dividend cut would be implemented from the first quarter of 2015.